Atlantic Map, Summer 1940

Eric Rauchway

2022-06-21

Map data draws principally from Natural Earth datasets, at various resolutions. I’ve drawn for reference on other sources, including André Ourednik’s historical basemaps repository and Michael de Groot’s “Building the New Order” as well as the Rand-McNally map of Africa in 1939, from the David Rumsey Map Collection; for names of bases, Air Corps News Letter For colors I drew mainly from CARTOcolors. When all else has failed I’ve looked up latitudes and longitudes in Wikipedia.
